  "text": "is the vector of explanatory variables that we control for when estimating unpaid and paid work time. Except for the instrumental variable incorporated in , includes all the independent variables used in the first step (age and age squared, education years, interaction variable for education and age, and ownership of domestic appliances). In addition to these variables, we also control for the variables that may affect both unemployment risk and work time. Urban/rural (0/1) residence and the number of children (by sex and age group: older than 15 years of age and younger than 16) are our additional controls. Based on other country experiences, we expect to get a positive relationship between unpaid work time and urban/rural dummy and the reverse might be obtained for paid work time [CITATION_1] .",
